disableTlsVerify.description:
`disable_tls_verify` controls whether a client verifies the server's certificate chain and host name. default it is set
to `true`. If `disable_tls_verify` is true, crypto/tls accepts any certificate presented by the server and any host name
in that certificate. In this mode, TLS is susceptible to machine-in-the-middle attacks unless custom verification is
used. can be provided by `DISABLE_TLS_VERIFY` environment variable. > **NOTE** If it is set to `false`, certificate/ca
certificates should be added to `trusted store` of host where we are running this provider.

[UserManagement](https://techdocs.f5.com/en-us/f5os-a-1-4-0/f5-rseries-systems-administration-configuration/title-user-mgmt.html)

provider.description:
The provider type for the f5os package. By default, resources use package-wide configuration
settings, however an explicit `Provider` instance may be created and passed during resource
construction to achieve fine-grained programmatic control over provider settings. See the
[documentation](https://www.pulumi.com/docs/reference/programming-model/#providers) for more information.

configurationVolumeSize.description:
select the desired configuration volume in increments of 1 GB. The default value is 10 GB, with a minimum of 5 GB and a
maximum of 15 GB.After volume sizes are configured, their sizes can be increased but not reduced

imagesVolumeSize.description:
select the desired storage volume for all tenant images in increments of 1 GB. The default value is 15 GB, with a
minimum of 5 GB and a maximum of 50 GB.After volume sizes are configured, their sizes can be increased but not reduced

ipv4MgmtAddress.description:
Specifies the IPv4 address and subnet mask used to access the chassis partition. The address must be specified in CIDR
notation e.g. 192.168.1.1/24.

ipv4MgmtGateway.description: Specifies the IPv4 chassis partition management gateway.

ipv6MgmtAddress.description:
Specifies the IPv6 address and subnet mask used to access the chassis partition. The address must be specified in CIDR
notation e.g. 2002::1234:abcd:ffff:c0a8:101/64. Required for create operations.

ipv6MgmtGateway.description: Specifies the IPv6 chassis partition management gateway. Required for create operations.

name.description:
Name of the chassis partition. Partition names must consist only of alphanumerics (0-9, a-z, A-Z), must begin with a
letter, and are limited to 31 characters.

osVersion.description: Specifies the partition F5OS-C OS Bundled version.(ISO image version)

sharedVolumeSize.description:

cryptos.description:
Whether crypto and compression hardware offload should be enabled on the tenant. We recommend it is enabled, otherwise
crypto and compression may be processed in CPU.

imageName.description: Name of the tenant image to be used. Required for create operations

macBlockSize.description: Configure a BIG-IP tenant on these systems to use contiguous block of MAC allocation. Default value is `one`.

memory.description:
The amount of memory that should be provided to the tenant in MB. More information on memory sizing for
[Velos](https://clouddocs.f5.com/training/community/velos-training/html/velos_performance_and_sizing.html#memory-sizing)/[rSeries](https://clouddocs.f5.com/training/community/rseries-training/html/rseries_performance_and_sizing.html#memory-sizing)

mgmtIp.description: IP address used to connect to the deployed tenant. Required for create operations.

name.description:
Name of the tenant. The first character must be a letter. Only lowercase alphanumeric characters are allowed. No special
or extended characters are allowed except for hyphens. The name cannot exceed 50 characters.

nodes.description:
List of integers. Specifies on which blades nodes the tenants are deployed. Required for create operations. For single
blade platforms like rSeries only the value of 1 should be provided.

timeout.description: The number of seconds to wait for image import to finish.

type.description: Name of the tenant image to be used. Required for create operations

city.description: The residing cty of the certificate holder.

confirmKeyPassphrase.description:
This specifies the confirmation of the passphrase for the key, the value should be the same as the `key_passphrase`.
This attribute is required when `key_type` is set to `encrypted-rsa` or `encrypted-ecdsa`

country.description: The residing country of the certificate holder.

daysValid.description: The number of days for which the certificate is valid, the default value is 30 days

email.description: The email address of the certificate holder.

keyCurve.description:
This specifies the specific elliptic curve used in ECC, this is only applicable for ECDSA keys. This attribute is
required when `key_type` is set to `ecdsa` or `encrypted-ecdsa`

keyPassphrase.description:
This specifies the passphrase for the key. This attribute is required when `key_type` is set to `encrypted-rsa` or
`encrypted-ecdsa`

keySize.description:
This specifies the length of the key, this is only applicable for RSA keys. This attribute is required when `key_type`
is set to `rsa` or `encrypted-rsa`

keyType.description: The type of the tls key

name.description: Name of the tls certificate.

organization.description: The organization of the certificate holder

province.description: The residing province of the certificate holder.

subjectAlternativeName.description:
The subject alternative name of the tls certificate. This attribute is required for F5OS v1.8 and above and not
supported for F5OS below v1.8

unit.description: The organizational unit of the certificate holder.

city.description: The residing cty of the certificate holder.

confirmKeyPassphrase.description:
This specifies the confirmation of the passphrase for the key, the value should be the same as the `key_passphrase`.

daysValid.description: The number of days for which the certificate is valid, the default value is 30 days

email.description: The email address of the certificate holder.
